Net-LDAP-AutoDNs

Automatically make some default decisions some LDAP DNs and scopes.

Currently supported methodes are environmental and hostname.

use Net::LDAP::AutoDNs;

my $obj = Net::LDAP::AutoDNs->new();

print $obj->{users}."\n";
print $obj->{usersScope}."\n";
print $obj->{dns}."\n";
print $obj->{dnsScope}."\n";
print $obj->{groups}."\n";
print $obj->{groupsScope}."\n";
print $obj->{home}."\n";
print $obj->{homeScope}."\n";

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

/DEV/LDAP

The FreeBSD kernel module for this can be found at
http://eesdp.org/eesdp/ldap-kmod.html .

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Net::LDAP::AutoDNs

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Net-LDAP-AutoDNs

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Net-LDAP-AutoDNs

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Net-LDAP-AutoDNs

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Net-LDAP-AutoDNs


